                                GIF Search and Actor POST API

Project Overview
This project is a web application that allows users to search for GIFs and post actor details with their movies to a mock API. The application has a user-friendly interface where users can input search terms to fetch GIFs from Giphy and submit actor information, including a list of movies, to a fictional API endpoint.

Features
GIF Search: Search for GIFs using a query input. The GIFs are displayed in a responsive grid layout -Currently set to repsonse with 50 GIFs.

Loading Indicator: Displays a loading wheel while fetching GIFs and hides it once the data is loaded.

Error Handling: Displays an error message if no GIFs are found or if there is a fetch error.

Actor POST: Allows users to post actor details and movies to a mock API endpoint.

Responsive Design: The layout adjusts to different screen sizes using CSS media queries.

Technologies Used:
HTML:
Structure and content of the web page.
CSS:
Styling of the web page and components.
JavaScript:
index.js: Handles GIF search, display, and interaction.
api.js: Manages the POST request to a mock API and error handling.
load.js: Initializes the page with a default GIF.

How to Use:

Search for GIFs:
Enter a search term into the input field and click the "Submit" button or press Enter.
The application will fetch and display GIFs related to the search term.
If no GIFs are found, an error message will be displayed.

POST Actor Details:
Click the "Fetch: POST" button to start the process.
Provide the actor's first name, last name, and a comma-separated list of movies in the prompts.
The details will be submitted to the mock database, and a confirmation message will be displayed.
